## Composition Examples

### Secondary Toolbar Action

```vue
<template>
  <TxFlex align="center" gap="8px">
    <TuffFlatButton @click="refresh">Refresh</TuffFlatButton>
    <TuffFlatButton primary @click="openDetails">View details</TuffFlatButton>
  </TxFlex>
</template>
```

### Async Action

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const saving = ref(false)

async function save() {
  if (saving.value) return
  saving.value = true
  try {
    await api.save()
  }
  finally {
    saving.value = false
  }
}
</script>

<template>
  <TuffFlatButton :loading="saving" @click="save">
    Save changes
  </TuffFlatButton>
</template>
```

## Interaction Contract

- The root is a native `<button type="button">`, so it does not submit parent forms by default.
- `disabled` and `loading` both set the native `disabled` attribute and block `click` emission.
- `loading` adds `.is-loading`, renders `.tx-flat-button__loading` with an inline SVG spinner, and keeps the default slot content visible.
- `primary` adds `.is-primary` and removes the non-primary `fake-background` class.
- Non-primary buttons keep `fake-background` and set hover background through `--fake-color`.
- `mini` adds `.is-mini`, reducing min width and horizontal padding without changing semantics.
- Enabled clicks emit the original `MouseEvent`.
- The component installs globally under `TuffFlatButton`, not `TxFlatButton`.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `primary` | `boolean` | `false` | Use primary visual styling. |
| `mini` | `boolean` | `false` | Use compact size styling. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disable native button and block click emits. |
| `loading` | `boolean` | `false` | Show spinner, disable native button, and block click emits. |

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `click` | `MouseEvent` | Emitted only when `disabled=false` and `loading=false`. |

### Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `default` | - | Button label/content. Remains visible during loading. |

## Best Practices

- Use `TuffFlatButton` for secondary or local actions. Use `TxButton` for full variant, native type, border, vibration, or stronger hierarchy needs.
- Bind `loading` to async mutations to prevent duplicate submissions.
- Do not rely on `primary` to mean destructive or success. Pair important states with explicit text.
- Use `mini` for dense toolbars, not for primary form actions.
- Since the component always uses `type="button"`, use `TxButton native-type="submit"` when a form submit button is required.

